  'hamilton-heights': `Hamilton Heights presents the full scope of Manhattan pest challenges — pre-war building infrastructure with connected basement systems, dense residential and commercial activity creating food-waste pressure at street level, and a high-turnover rental market that continuously introduces bed bugs through used furniture and transient tenants. Whether you’re in a pre-war co-op, a newer high-rise, or a commercial space, Jet Pest Control’s Manhattan technicians will arrive discreetly, inspect thoroughly, and treat effectively. We serve Hamilton Heights with same-day appointments and the professional protocols that building managers and tenants in this neighborhood expect.`,
  'harlem': `Harlem's cultural renaissance has brought new restaurants, boutiques, and renovated brownstones alongside the neighborhood's historic fabric — but the underlying building stock, much of it 1890s–1920s row houses and five-story tenements, retains the structural characteristics that drive persistent pest pressure. Connected brownstone blocks along 125th Street and the numbered cross streets allow rodent and cockroach populations to move between buildings without outdoor exposure. NYCHA developments in East and Central Harlem experience some of Manhattan's most elevated cockroach and rodent pressure. Marcus Garvey Park's wooded slopes deliver wildlife pressure to bordering residential buildings. Jet Pest Control serves all of Harlem — central, west, and east — with same-day service and whole-building treatment programs for co-ops and multi-family landlords.`,
  'hells-kitchen': `Hell's Kitchen — rebranded as Clinton but still Hell's Kitchen to those who live there — is defined by its Restaurant Row on 46th Street and the dense concentration of hospitality workers and service industry employees who rent the neighborhood's pre-war apartments. The extraordinary restaurant density between 9th and 10th Avenues generates one of Manhattan's most active food-waste ecosystems, sustaining rat populations in alley trash areas that migrate directly into the residential buildings above and adjacent. Cockroach pressure from commercial kitchens reaches residential units through shared walls and plumbing chases. The transient nature of the neighborhood — many residents are theater workers, hotel staff, and culinary students — increases bed bug introduction risk through used furniture and frequent subletting. Jet Pest Control serves Hell's Kitchen with both commercial kitchen programs and residential treatment.`,
