  'stuyvesant-town': `Manhattan’s pest environment is relentless, and Stuyvesant Town is no exception. The pre-war co-ops and newer glass towers of residential and commercial buildings here creates a layered challenge: rodents entering through basement service entrances, cockroaches migrating between connected units through plumbing chases, and bed bugs introduced through the constant churn of furnished apartments. Jet Pest Control serves Stuyvesant Town with discreet, professional service — unmarked vehicles, flexible scheduling, and treatment protocols that don’t disrupt your neighbors or your building management. Same-day available.`,
  'tribeca': `Tribeca's cobblestone streets and landmark cast-iron loft buildings set the stage for one of Manhattan's most aesthetically distinctive — and pest-complex — neighborhoods. The 19th-century commercial buildings converted to luxury residential lofts retain loading docks, freight elevators, and basement-level former storage floors where rodents can establish without ever being detected on the residential floors above. Hudson River Park's landscaped waterfront borders Tribeca's western edge, and the wildlife it attracts — rats, raccoons, waterfowl — creates ongoing pressure against building basements along Greenwich and Washington Streets. The neighborhood's boutique restaurant scene on Duane and Reade Streets drives cockroach pressure in adjacent buildings. Jet Pest Control handles Tribeca's loft buildings with the targeted precision that historic structure preservation demands.`,
  'upper-east-side': `The Upper East Side is Manhattan's most established residential enclave — pre-war limestone co-ops along Park and Fifth Avenues, post-war brick high-rises on the cross streets, and the newer glass towers along Second and Third Avenues all share the same pest challenges that altitude alone can't prevent. Bed bugs are a persistent concern in furnished apartments near the 4/5/6 train stations, where transient subletters and short-term rentals increase introduction risk. Rodents enter through basement service entrances and loading docks common to every pre-war building along the avenues. German cockroaches ride up in grocery deliveries and establish in kitchen walls. Jet Pest Control serves the Upper East Side with the discreet, professional protocols that building managers and co-op boards demand — technicians arrive in unmarked vehicles, and treatments are scheduled around residents' routines.`,
  'upper-west-side': `The Upper West Side's character — prewar apartment buildings along West End Avenue and Riverside Drive, the Collegiate Gothic towers of Columbia's neighbor community, the Lincoln Center cultural campus — comes with a pest profile shaped by century-old infrastructure. Riverside Park's wooded hillside borders dozens of buildings directly, delivering raccoon, squirrel, and rat pressure through basement-level service entrances. The neighborhood's abundance of pre-war buildings with original plumbing, dumbwaiter shafts, and connected basements creates pathways that pest populations exploit across entire buildings. Bed bugs are a consistent concern in furnished rentals near Columbia and the music schools. Jet Pest Control serves all of the Upper West Side with treatments designed for pre-war building infrastructure — thorough, discreet, and proven.`,
