  'freeport': `Freeport's Nautical Mile — a waterfront strip of restaurants, marinas, and fish markets on Woodcleft Canal — is the heart of one of Nassau County's most distinctive communities. The commercial waterfront generates significant food waste that sustains rat populations which spread into the dense residential streets behind the canal. The boat yards and marine storage facilities harbor rodents year-round in vessels and equipment storage. Freeport's residential streets, a mix of post-war single-family homes and apartment buildings, are subject to elevated moisture-related pest pressure from the surrounding waterways. The neighborhood's summer festival season intensifies commercial pest pressure. Jet Pest Control serves Freeport's homes, restaurants, and marine businesses with treatments appropriate for waterfront environments.`,
  'garden-city': `Garden City is one of Long Island's most prestigious planned communities — a 1869 grid of tree-lined streets, single-family colonial and Tudor homes, and a thriving commercial district along Seventh Street that makes it Nassau County's premier suburban address. The neighborhood's mature trees and manicured landscaping create ideal tick habitat in backyard leaf litter, with black-legged tick pressure particularly high in the spring and fall seasons. Older homes along Stewart Avenue and the Vanderbilt corridor have crawlspace and basement systems that attract rodents during winter months. Garden City's large co-op apartment complexes along Franklin Avenue experience cockroach pressure in shared laundry and utility spaces. Jet Pest Control serves Garden City with the discreet, professional service that this neighborhood's homeowners and property managers expect.`,
