  'jericho': `Jericho is a well-established Nassau County community where the suburban residential landscape creates pest conditions specific to Long Island’s North Shore geography. Aging ranch and colonial homes have basement and crawlspace systems that attract rodents during fall and winter months. Nassau County’s mix of mature tree cover and proximity to the coast creates tick habitat on most residential lots, with black-legged tick pressure active from April through November. Ant supercolonies are a persistent spring and summer challenge in the dense suburban grid. Jet Pest Control serves Jericho with the full range of Long Island residential pest services — rodent exclusion, tick treatments, termite inspections, and more.`,
  'lawrence': `Pest control in Lawrence reflects Nassau County’s suburban character: single-family homes with crawlspaces and finished basements where rodents winter, manicured lawns with tick pressure from white-tailed deer, and the termite vulnerability common to Long Island’s aging housing stock. Jet Pest Control has deep roots in Nassau County and serves Lawrence with the same thoroughness we bring to every Long Island community. Whether it’s a rodent exclusion, a termite inspection, or a mosquito treatment for your backyard, we’re available today.`,
  'levittown': `Levittown is the original American suburb — 17,000 nearly identical Cape Cod homes built between 1947 and 1951 by William Levitt, now aging into their eighth decade of occupancy. The uniformity of construction means that pest vulnerabilities are uniformly shared: the same foundation design, the same attic access points, the same basement crawlspace configuration across thousands of adjacent homes. Rodents entering through original foundation gaps travel the entire neighborhood. Termite pressure is elevated throughout Levittown due to the original construction's use of untreated lumber in contact with soil — a design flaw Levitt didn't anticipate. The dense suburban layout and shared property lines also create conditions for ant supercolonies that span multiple lots. Jet Pest Control serves Levittown with neighborhood-wide experience in these specific construction types.`,
  'lido-beach': `Lido Beach is a well-established Nassau County community where the suburban residential landscape creates pest conditions specific to Long Island’s North Shore geography. Aging ranch and colonial homes have basement and crawlspace systems that attract rodents during fall and winter months. Nassau County’s mix of mature tree cover and proximity to the coast creates tick habitat on most residential lots, with black-legged tick pressure active from April through November. Ant supercolonies are a persistent spring and summer challenge in the dense suburban grid. Jet Pest Control serves Lido Beach with the full range of Long Island residential pest services — rodent exclusion, tick treatments, termite inspections, and more.`,
