  'hauppauge': `Hauppauge Industrial Park is one of the largest industrial parks in the US — over 1,300 companies on 1,500 acres — and the residential community surrounding it faces pest pressures directly tied to that commercial ecosystem. Rodent populations from the industrial park's loading docks and dumpsters migrate into nearby residential neighborhoods during seasonal transitions. The suburban grid of 1960s and 1970s ranch homes around Veterans Memorial Highway have basement and crawlspace systems that require annual attention. The park's food service tenants generate cockroach pressure that reaches commercial tenants in adjacent spaces. Jet Pest Control serves both Hauppauge's residential neighborhoods and the industrial park with commercial-grade programs for manufacturing, food service, and office tenants.`,
  'holbrook': `Holbrook is part of Suffolk County’s varied landscape — where suburban residential neighborhoods meet wooded lots, coastal marshes, and the agricultural character of Long Island’s eastern reach. That natural environment creates year-round pest pressure: black-legged ticks from deer movement, rodents seeking winter shelter in attics and crawlspaces, and the subterranean termite pressure that affects virtually all of Suffolk’s aging housing stock. Jet Pest Control serves Holbrook with Long Island’s most comprehensive residential pest programs — from tick treatments to termite inspections to rodent exclusion.`,
