  'sagaponack': `Sagaponack is part of Suffolk County’s varied landscape — where suburban residential neighborhoods meet wooded lots, coastal marshes, and the agricultural character of Long Island’s eastern reach. That natural environment creates year-round pest pressure: black-legged ticks from deer movement, rodents seeking winter shelter in attics and crawlspaces, and the subterranean termite pressure that affects virtually all of Suffolk’s aging housing stock. Jet Pest Control serves Sagaponack with Long Island’s most comprehensive residential pest programs — from tick treatments to termite inspections to rodent exclusion.`,
  'saint-james': `Saint James is part of Suffolk County’s varied landscape — where suburban residential neighborhoods meet wooded lots, coastal marshes, and the agricultural character of Long Island’s eastern reach. That natural environment creates year-round pest pressure: black-legged ticks from deer movement, rodents seeking winter shelter in attics and crawlspaces, and the subterranean termite pressure that affects virtually all of Suffolk’s aging housing stock. Jet Pest Control serves Saint James with Long Island’s most comprehensive residential pest programs — from tick treatments to termite inspections to rodent exclusion.`,
  'sayville': `Suffolk County’s Sayville community faces the full range of Long Island pest challenges. Mature trees and natural buffer zones create excellent tick habitat. Aging homes — many built in the 1950s through 1970s — have foundation systems that invite rodent entry during winter. Subterranean termites are active throughout this part of Suffolk County, and carpenter ant pressure is elevated wherever moisture contacts wood framing. Jet Pest Control covers Sayville with the same thoroughness we bring to every Suffolk service — same-day available, licensed technicians, written guarantee.`,
